.TH "cgroup_addrm_files" 9 "cgroup_addrm_files" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cgroup_addrm_files \- add or remove files to a cgroup directory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cgroup_addrm_files
.BI "(struct cgroup_subsys_state *css "  ","
.BI "struct cgroup *cgrp "  ","
.BI "struct cftype cfts[] "  ","
.BI "bool is_add "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "css" 12
the target css
.IP "cgrp" 12
the target cgroup (usually css->cgroup)
.IP "cfts" 12
array of cftypes to be added
.IP "is_add" 12
whether to add or remove
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Depending on \fIis_add\fP, add or remove files defined by \fIcfts\fP on \fIcgrp\fP.
For removals, this function never fails.
